QEMU\n     - Parameters: `--vlen N`, `--strace`, `--perf`, `--timeout N`\n     - Strace mode captures output from QEMU's fd 9 via `strace -f -e trace=write`\n     - Requires libnn.a already built (no --skip-build needed, just run build_libnn.sh first)\n\n   - `/home/nick/work/libnn/qemu-validate/run_fpga_test.sh` (NEW, ~190 lines)\n     - FPGA benchmark runner — compiles test binary and runs on FPGA board\n     - Parameters: `--port N`, `--host H`, `--perf`, `--tag NAME`\n     - Key flags: `-mvh`, `-DGETENV_TESTDIR=\"${UNIT_TEST_DIR}\"`, `-DENA_RUN_TWICE`\n     - Deletes `First_Reset_done` before each run for clean board state\n     - Saves results to log files in `qemu-validate/work/`\n\n   - `/home/nick/work/libnn/Examples/unit_func/run.sh`\n     - Was temporarily modified (ENA_TEST_ALL=0, ENA_CONV_TEST=1, CONV array reduced to single entry) for testing\n     - **Fully restored** to original state at end\n\n   - `/home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/run.sh`\n     - Project test runner, RUN_CONFIG=2 (QEMU), default wrapper v512_d512_b512\n     - Builds library then delegates to Examples/unit_func/run.sh\n\n   - `/home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/riscv-qemu-wrapper-v512_d512_b512`\n     - QEMU wrapper: andes-ax45mpv CPU, vext_spec=v1.0, vlen=512, andes_ae350 machine, semihosting\n\n   - `/home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/riscv64-sim-wrapper-on-board`\n     - FPGA board wrapper: uses GDB expect script `gdb-ice-riscv64.exp`\n\n   - `/home/nick/work/libnn/Examples/unit_func/include/test_util.h`\n     - Line 104-111: `#ifdef GETENV_TESTDIR` controls how golden data files are found — with it defined, uses absolute path `sprintf(path_buffer, \"%s/bin/%s\", xstr(GETENV_TESTDIR), fName)`\n\n   - `/home/nick/work/libnn/Source/NNSupportFunctions/nn_mat_mult_kernel_s8_offset.c`\n     - Contains `nn_mat_mult_kernel_s8_offset_v2` at line 1728 — the vd4dots-based GEMM kernel used by the optimization\n\n4. Errors and fixes:\n   - **QEMU produces no output**: Discovered via strace that QEMU writes semihosting output to fd 9 (not stdout/fd 1), returning EBADF. This is a Claude Code sandbox issue where QEMU's chardev fd isn't connected to the terminal. Fix: use `strace -f -e trace=write` to capture output. The actual test results showed all 3 sub-tests PASS.\n   \n   - **CWD issues running run.sh**: Multiple attempts to run project/ax45mpv/run.sh failed because CWD was /home/nick/work/libnn instead of project/ax45mpv, causing `cd ../../` to go to wrong directory and `build.sh: command not found`. Fix: explicitly cd to project/ax45mpv before running.\n   \n   - **head -100 killed pipeline via SIGPIPE**: Using `| head -100` on run.sh output caused the entire pipeline to be killed before tests could execute. Fix: removed head, used full output capture.\n   \n   - **FPGA port 1116 timeout, port 1117 connection reset**: Board connectivity issues. User suggested trying port 1116 again, which worked.\n   \n   - **FPGA \"Error on opening 8b_in1.bin\"**: GDB semihosting resolves file paths relative to GDB's working directory, not the binary's location. The golden data files in `Examples/unit_func/bin/` couldn't be found. Fix: add `-DGETENV_TESTDIR=/home/nick/work/libnn/Examples/unit_func` to compilation, which makes the test binary use absolute paths to find `bin/*.bin` files.\n   \n   - **FPGA exception \"Environment call from M-mode\"**: First FPGA attempt crashed because binary was compiled with wrong flags (missing proper FPGA setup). Fix: ensured `-mvh` flag for semihosting, and used `ENA_MEASURE_PERF=1` for perf-only mode.\n   \n   - **User feedback \"why full test suite? not just single API executable?\"**: I was about to run test.sh which rebuilds the entire library + runs all tests. User wanted just the single test. Fix: compiled single test binary manually and ran via board wrapper directly.\n   \n   - **User feedback \"separate libnn build from runner\"**: Initial scripts combined build + test in one. Refactored into 3 separate scripts: build_libnn.sh, run_qemu_test.sh, run_fpga_test.sh.\n   \n   - **User feedback \"try compile binary with -mvh\"**: User pointed out that `-mvh` is needed for semihosting I/O output on both QEMU and FPGA.\n\n5. Problem Solving:\n   - Successfully validated optimization via QEMU (strace workaround): all 3 sub-tests pass\n   - Successfully benchmarked on FPGA with fair A/B comparison:\n     - Baseline: 3,826,922 inst / 5,456,391 cycles\n     - Optimized: 1,039,912 inst / 2,187,394 cycles\n     - **2.49x cycle speedup, 3.68x instruction reduction**\n   - Created reusable 3-script infrastructure for future optimize→validate→benchmark workflow\n   - /simplify review completed (3 agents returned findings) but fixes not yet applied\n\n6. All user messages:\n   - (Context from previous conversation summary - user asked to pick most profitable function, optimize, verify via QEMU, if PASS run on FPGA)\n   - \"what are you doing now? any problem?\"\n   - \"try compile binary with -mvh\"\n   - \"go ahead\" (for FPGA benchmarking)\n   - \"board port 1117\"\n   - \"try port 1116\"\n   - \"what is baseline?\"\n   - \"yes !\" (to running fair A/B comparison with same flags)\n   - \"Now, let's review what you have solved. First, QEMU and FPGA runner, write into two scripts to ensure smooth running next time. (remember to parameterize)\"\n   - \"separate libnn build from runner (QEMU and FPGA)\"\n   - (invoked /simplify command)\n\n7. Pending Tasks:\n   - Apply fixes from /simplify review (3 agents completed, findings aggregated, fixes not yet applied)\n   - Key issues to fix from review:\n     - C code: Remove dead code `pWt += 0;`, consider extracting vector requantize helper, address magic number `64`, fix im2col loop bound recalculation\n     - Shell scripts: Fix compilation flags divergence between QEMU (-mext-vector=${VEC_CFG}) and FPGA (-mext-vector without VEC_CFG), fix FPGA script EXIT_CODE logic error (set -e kills before capture), remove unused EXIT_CODE variable\n   - Restore Examples/unit_func/run.sh CONV array if not already done (it was restored)\n\n8. Current Work:\n   The /simplify workflow was invoked. Three review agents completed and returned findings:\n   \n   **Agent 1 (Code Reuse)**: Found vector requantize sequence repeated 5x in same file (HIGH priority to extract helper). Shell scripts duplicate path resolution and toolchain setup.\n   \n   **Agent 2 (Code Quality)**: Found dead code `pWt += 0;` (line 564), leftover handler duplicates nn_mat_mult_kernel_s8_offset_v2 logic (80+ lines, HIGH severity), magic number 64, compilation flags diverge between QEMU/FPGA scripts (QEMU uses `-mext-vector=${VEC_CFG}` but FPGA uses `-mext-vector` without VEC_CFG), EXIT_CODE variable in FPGA script never used due to set -e.\n   \n   **Agent 3 (Efficiency)**: Single-channel processing in leftover loop (HIGH - should process 2 channels like the kernel), redundant VRSUB_VX per channel iteration (could hoist), im2col bound recalculation (pre-compute `cur_out_y * stride_y - pad_y`).\n   \n   The /simplify instructions say: \"Wait for all three agents to complete. Aggregate their findings and fix each issue directly.\"\n\n9. Optional Next Step:\n   Per the /simplify workflow: \"Aggregate their findings and fix each issue directly. If a finding is a false positive or not worth addressing, note it and move on.\"\n   \n   All three agents have completed. The next step is to aggregate findings and apply fixes to:\n   - `Source/ConvolutionFunctions/riscv_nn_conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any.c` (remove dead code, fix im2col bounds, address magic number)\n   - `qemu-validate/run_fpga_test.sh` (fix compilation flags to use VEC_CFG, fix set -e/EXIT_CODE issue)\n   - `qemu-validate/run_qemu_test.sh` (ensure flag consistency with FPGA script)\n   \n   Note: Some findings (extracting vector requantize helper, refactoring leftover to process 2 channels) are significant refactors that may not be appropriate to apply in a /simplify pass without user confirmation, as they could affect correctness of the already-validated 2.49x optimization.\n\nIf you need specific details from before compaction (like exact code snippets, error messages, or content you generated), read the full transcript at: /home/nick/.claude/projects/-home-nick-work-libnn/82014f9c-9ec8-4644-b937-5518fb054df0.jsonl\nContinue the conversation from where it left off without asking the user any further questions. Resume directly — do not acknowledge the summary, do not recap what was happening, do not preface with \"I'll continue\" or similar. Pick up the last task as if the break never happened."},"isVisibleInTranscriptOnly":true,"isCompactSummary":true,"uuid":"ad63b9ac-62e3-41ff-9cf4-55fa4944a1ce","timestamp":"2026-03-20T13:33:55.109Z"}
