{"parentUuid":"42b57095-15d5-4747-989b-c7cd316b2f60","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/nick/work/libnn","sessionId":"82014f9c-9ec8-4644-b937-5518fb054df0","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"develop","agentId":"acompact-5b317e2189e1a3bb","slug":"snug-orbiting-tower","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01MSGx8qXoHA3YwaBF23JuHq","type":"tool_result","content":"---\nname: qemu-validate\ndescription: \"QEMU functional validation for libnn on Andes AX45MPV. Use when verifying correctness of libnn functions after code changes. Triggers on: validate, QEMU test, functional test, accuracy check, run tests, verify correctness, unit test.\"\n---\n\n# QEMU Functional Validation for libnn\n\nBuild and run libnn unit tests on QEMU to verify functional correctness after code changes.\n\n## Environment Setup\n\n```bash\nexport QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64\nexport PATH=\"/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH\"\n```\n\n## Running All Unit Tests\n\nThe full test suite runs 294 unit tests via the project run.sh script:\n\n```bash\ncd /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv\nexport QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64\nexport PATH=\"/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH\"\nbash ./run.sh\n```\n\n- `run.sh` uses `RUN_CONFIG=2` (QEMU mode) by default\n- Default VLEN=512 (`riscv-qemu-wrapper-v512_d512_b512`)\n- To change VLEN, edit `RUN_WRAPPER` in `run.sh` (line ~101)\n\n### Available QEMU VLEN configurations\n\n| Wrapper script | VLEN | DLEN | BLEN |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v128_d128_b128` | 128 | 128 | 128 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v256_d128_b128` | 256 | 128 | 128 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v256_d256_b256` | 256 | 256 | 256 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v512_d256_b256` | 512 | 256 | 256 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v512_d512_b512` | 512 | 512 | 512 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d512_b512` | 1024 | 512 | 512 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d1024_b512` | 1024 | 1024 | 512 |\n\nUser's primary target: **VLEN=1024** (`riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d1024_b512`)\n\n## Running a Single Test\n\nTo quickly validate a single function after editing:\n\n```bash\nexport QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64\nexport PATH=\"/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH\"\n\n# 1. Rebuild the library\ncd /home/nick/work/libnn\nbuild.sh AX45MPV\n\n# 2. Compile the test\ncd /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv\nCC=riscv64-elf-gcc\nCFLAGS=\"-mtune=andes-45-series -mext-vector -DNDS_VEC_RVV_VERSION=1000 -O3 -Wall -Werror -ffunction-sections -fdata-sections -DPF_COUNTER -Wl,-gc-sections -DENA_FS_VS -mvh -DFAST_VERSION -DFUNCTION_PF_ANALYZE -mzfh -DENA_VL4\"\nINC=\"-I../../Examples/unit_func/include -I../../Include -I../../internal\"\nLIB=\"-L../../release -lnn_v -lm\"\nFUNC_NAME=\"<function_name>\"  # e.g., conv_1x1_HWC_s8_s8_s8_sym_bias_fast_any\n$CC $CFLAGS $INC -o t_${FUNC_NAME}.adx ../../Examples/unit_func/t_${FUNC_NAME}.c $LIB\n\n# 3. Run via QEMU\n./riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d1024_b512 t_${FUNC_NAME}.adx\n```\n\nExpected output contains `pass` for successful accuracy verification.\n\n## Workflow: Validate After Optimization\n\nTypical workflow after modifying a function's RVV implementation:\n\n1. **Rebuild library**: `cd /home/nick/work/libnn && build.sh AX45MPV`\n2. **Quick single-function test**: Compile and run the specific test via QEMU (see above)\n3. **Full regression**: Run all 294 tests via `run.sh` to check nothing else broke\n4. **Performance measurement**: Use the `fpga-bench` skill on FPGA board for cycle counts","is_error":false}]},"uuid":"34e86c0a-fa0d-4897-a863-4c6616a65490","timestamp":"2026-03-20T22:54:14.488Z","toolUseResult":{"stdout":"---\nname: qemu-validate\ndescription: \"QEMU functional validation for libnn on Andes AX45MPV. Use when verifying correctness of libnn fu