{"parentUuid":"d214a8fd-000a-4453-998b-ae3c2f9ff654","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/nick/work/libnn","sessionId":"82014f9c-9ec8-4644-b937-5518fb054df0","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"develop","agentId":"acompact-5b317e2189e1a3bb","slug":"snug-orbiting-tower","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01QakipWQc7acddBtsCJp86F","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_013ujjSANiLkntob6yZPwp9K","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/skill-build/qemu-validate/SKILL.md","content":"---\nname: qemu-validate\ndescription: \"QEMU functional validation for libnn on Andes AX45MPV. Use when verifying correctness of libnn functions after code changes. Triggers on: validate, QEMU test, functional test, accuracy check, run tests, verify correctness, unit test.\"\n---\n\n# QEMU Functional Validation for libnn\n\nBuild and run libnn unit tests on QEMU to verify functional correctness after code changes.\n\n## Quick Start (Recommended)\n\nUse the scripts in `qemu-validate/`:\n\n```bash\ncd /home/nick/work/libnn/qemu-validate\n\n# Step 1: Build the library\nbash build_libnn.sh --verbose\n\n# Step 2: Run a single function test on QEMU\nbash run_qemu_test.sh conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any --strace\n```\n\n### build_libnn.sh\n\nBuilds `libnn.a` for a target CPU. Must run before QEMU or FPGA tests.\n\n```bash\nbash build_libnn.sh [--cpu NAME] [--vec-cfg CFG] [--verbose]\n```\n\n| Option | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `--cpu NAME` | ax45mpv | CPU build target |\n| `--vec-cfg CFG` | zve64d | Vector config: zve32x, zve32f, zve64x, zve64f, zve64d |\n| `--verbose` | off | Show full build output |\n\n### run_qemu_test.sh\n\nCompiles a single unit test against `libnn.a` and runs it on QEMU.\n\n```bash\nbash run_qemu_test.sh <test_name> [--vlen N] [--strace] [--perf] [--timeout N]\n```\n\n| Option | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `--vlen N` | 512 | Vector length: 128, 256, 512, 1024 |\n| `--strace` | off | Capture output via strace (needed in sandboxed environments) |\n| `--perf` | off | Performance mode: run only the large test case |\n| `--timeout N` | 120 | QEMU timeout in seconds |\n\n**Important**: Always use `--strace` when running from Claude Code, as QEMU's semihosting output goes to a non-stdout fd in sandboxed environments.\n\n## Correctness Verification\n\nEach unit test (`Examples/unit_func/t_*.c`) compares the function's output against pre-computed golden data stored in `Examples/unit_func/bin/*.bin`. The test prints:\n- `accuracy checking pass` — output matches golden data within tolerance\n- `accuracy checking fail` — mismatch detected\n\nMost tests have 3 sub-tests (small/medium/large input sizes). All must pass.\n\n## Running Full Test Suite\n\nFor full regression (294 unit tests):\n\n```bash\ncd /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv\nexport QEMU_SYS_RV64=/local/nick/qemu_andes/build/qemu-system-riscv64\nexport PATH=\"/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH\"\nbash ./run.sh\n```\n\n- `run.sh` uses `RUN_CONFIG=2` (QEMU mode) by default\n- Default VLEN=512 (`riscv-qemu-wrapper-v512_d512_b512`)\n\n### Available QEMU VLEN configurations\n\n| Wrapper script | VLEN | DLEN | BLEN |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v128_d128_b128` | 128 | 128 | 128 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v256_d128_b128` | 256 | 128 | 128 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v256_d256_b256` | 256 | 256 | 256 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v512_d256_b256` | 512 | 256 | 256 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v512_d512_b512` | 512 | 512 | 512 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d512_b512` | 1024 | 512 | 512 |\n| `riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d1024_b512` | 1024 | 1024 | 512 |\n\nUser's primary target: **VLEN=1024** (`riscv-qemu-wrapper-v1024_d1024_b512`)\n\n## Workflow: Validate After Optimization\n\n1. **Rebuild library**: `bash build_libnn.sh --verbose`\n2. **Quick single-function test**: `bash run_qemu_test.sh <func_name> --strace`\n3. **Full regression** (if needed): Run `project/ax45mpv/run.sh`\n4. **Performance measurement**: Use the `fpga-bench` skill for FPGA cycle counts\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":426,"cache_read_input_tokens":51149,"output_tokens":1369,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":426,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZF9y2EGDA2Qz9r7Wa1gU","type":"assistant","uuid":"b08dadd7-34cb-4851-bc26-9977d5f2634d","timestamp":"2026-03-20T22:55:00.436Z"}
