{"parentUuid":"7de95c5c-c5ff-4e5b-837b-0cc974ef22e1","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/nick/work/libnn","sessionId":"82014f9c-9ec8-4644-b937-5518fb054df0","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"develop","agentId":"acompact-5b317e2189e1a3bb","slug":"snug-orbiting-tower","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011rTUijmVZk45RySCMqa2um","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_019o6tN1AxPGsprmmiMF2qgs","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/tmp/skill-build/fpga-bench/SKILL.md","content":"---\nname: fpga-bench\ndescription: \"FPGA benchmarking for libnn on Andes AX45MPV. Use when collecting, comparing, or analyzing cycle counts from FPGA board runs. Triggers on benchmark, performance comparison, cycle count, FPGA test results, perf regression, or performance.csv analysis.\"\n---\n\n# FPGA Benchmarking for libnn\n\nRecord, compare, and analyze cycle-accurate performance data from FPGA board runs of libnn on AX45MPV.\n\n## Quick Start (Recommended)\n\nUse the scripts in `qemu-validate/`:\n\n```bash\ncd /home/nick/work/libnn/qemu-validate\n\n# Step 1: Build the library (if not already built)\nbash build_libnn.sh --verbose\n\n# Step 2: Run a single function benchmark on FPGA\nbash run_fpga_test.sh conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any --perf --tag baseline\n```\n\n### run_fpga_test.sh\n\nCompiles a single unit test against `libnn.a` and runs it on the FPGA board via GDB/ICEman.\n\n```bash\nbash run_fpga_test.sh <test_name> [--port N] [--host H] [--perf] [--tag NAME]\n```\n\n| Option | Default | Description |\n|---|---|---|\n| `--port N` | 1116 | FPGA board port |\n| `--host H` | sw-boards.andestech.com | FPGA board host |\n| `--perf` | off | Performance mode: ENA_MEASURE_PERF=1, large test case only |\n| `--tag NAME` | (none) | Tag for log file naming (e.g. 'baseline', 'optimized') |\n\nKey compilation flags applied automatically:\n- `-mvh` — semihosting for GDB file I/O\n- `-DGETENV_TESTDIR=...` — absolute path so binary finds `bin/*.bin` golden data\n- `-DENA_RUN_TWICE` — runs function twice, measures warm-cache second run\n- `-mext-vector=zve64d` — consistent with build_libnn.sh and run_qemu_test.sh\n\nOutput: log file saved to `qemu-validate/work/<test_name>_<tag>.log` with inst/cycle counts and pass/fail status.\n\n### A/B Performance Comparison Workflow\n\n```bash\ncd /home/nick/work/libnn/qemu-validate\n\n# 1. Build and benchmark baseline\nbash build_libnn.sh --verbose\nbash run_fpga_test.sh <func_name> --perf --tag baseline\n\n# 2. Apply optimization, rebuild and benchmark\n# ... edit source code ...\nbash build_libnn.sh --verbose\nbash run_fpga_test.sh <func_name> --perf --tag optimized\n\n# 3. Compare results\ncat work/<func_name>_baseline.log\ncat work/<func_name>_optimized.log\n```\n\n## Full Suite Benchmark\n\nFor benchmarking all functions (takes several hours):\n\n```bash\ncd /home/nick/work/libnn/build_perf_ax45mpv\nexport PATH=\"/local/nick/SW_Release_cp/ast530/nds64le-elf-newlib-v5d/bin:/home/nick/work/libnn:$PATH\"\nexport MYPC=sw-boards.andestech.com\nexport MYPORT=1116\nrm -f /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/First_Reset_done\n../test.sh \"\" riscv64-elf-gcc \\\n  /home/nick/work/libnn/project/ax45mpv/riscv64-sim-wrapper-on-board \\\n  BOARD BS3 \\\n  \"-mtune=andes-45-series -mext-vector -DNDS_VEC_RVV_VERSION=1000 \\\n   -DENA_RUN_TWICE -DENA_CACHEABLE_ENV_SETUP -lnn_v -mzfh \\\n   -DENA_TEST_PERF -DENA_DUMP_PARAMETERS\"\n```\n\n### Data Location\n\nFull-suite results are stored in `build_perf_ax45mpv/test_sh_<YYYYMMDDHHMMSS>/`:\n```\nperformance.csv    # group, function, inst, cycle\nparameter.csv      # group, function, test parameters\naccuracy_fail_list # functions that failed accuracy check\nlog/               # per-function logs\nadx/               # compiled test binaries\n```\n\n### Comparing Full-Suite Runs\n\n```bash\n# Full comparison table\npython3 scripts/compare_perf.py old/performance.csv new/performance.csv\n\n# Per-group summary\npython3 scripts/compare_perf.py old/performance.csv new/performance.csv --summary\n\n# Show only regressions > 5%\npython3 scripts/compare_perf.py old/performance.csv new/performance.csv --regression --threshold 5\n\n# Top 10 biggest improvements in convolution\npython3 scripts/compare_perf.py old/performance.csv new/performance.csv --improvement --group convolution --top 10\n```\n\n## Performance CSV Format\n\n```\ngroup, function, inst, cycle\nactivation,relu_s8,316,3085,\nconvolution,conv_HWC_s8_s8_s8_asym_bias_any,1039912,2187394\n```\n\n## Board Troubleshooting\n\n- **Timeout/connection reset**: Try different ports (1116, 1117). The board may be in use.\n- **\"Error on opening .bin\"**: Ensure `-DGETENV_TESTDIR` is set (run_fpga_test.sh handles this automatically).\n- **\"Environment call from M-mode\"**: Binary may be missing `-mvh` flag (run_fpga_test.sh handles this automatically).\n- **First_Reset_done**: The script deletes this file before each run to ensure clean board initialization.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":116,"cache_read_input_tokens":52977,"output_tokens":1550,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":116,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"requestId":"req_011CZFA2J7pfzA5kTPj3o4ou","type":"assistant","uuid":"8275da27-1abc-4fae-a15d-f12ad4715a32","timestamp":"2026-03-20T22:55:51.173Z"}
